  This doesnt cover the annoying corpse/summon rez needed at times however. (Small raids generally don't need this) Nor does it cover keys.<br>
<br>
GENERAL POINTS:<br>
<br>
1) AOE is bad, never ever use AOE, especially on isle 1, you can cause aggro you wouldn't believe.<br>
2) Pets can be used on most isles, but on Spiroc isle the AOE the birds use can end upwith agroed pets breaking mez (bad) and isle 7 NEVER use pets except perhaps for last fight.<br>
3) COH, lev, gates and DMF don't work here. Yeah as usual any tough place useful spells won't work /rude Verant.<br>
4) Bring ALL items you need with you, ie reagents bring a TON.  See (5) as to why.<br>
5) When you fall off all your keys *poof*!! so do NOT fall off, avoid edges and beware of grav fluxing/Whirl Till Hurl mobs.<br>
6) You will need poison resist gear (and Disease though thats lesser) if you intend going to Bzzazzt Isle (Isle 6 bee isle as its known), and magic resist if fighting Dojorn.<br>
7) Do NOT sit down on mobs that split into more, such as the horse/pegasus mobs and the bees. The splits will home in on anyone dumb enough to be on their bum!<br>
8)  Never EVER use say around Sirran the Lunatic, watch pet commands if you have a macro with messages.<br>
9) Do not duel or hit other people with harmful spells of any type on isle one this is VERY important, on other isles you may get away with it but its best not to try or let it happen.<br>
10) Sirran and the boss mob on each isle has a despawn time, if you do not get the keys/kill boss to spawn sirran you are FUBARed until the isle repops which takes 8-24 hours generally. Despawns usually 80 mins on boss mobs and 20 mins on Sirran.<br>
11) Watch out for flying mobs as they can end up to high for melee tohit, your pet can get stuck on them keeping them out of reach, so kill the pet.<br>
12) Many mobs are hit only by lures from isle 4+, so DS all tanks, and use pets when can. Personally I often volunteer for the Death Touch after dropping mod rods and DS tanks. Great fun to make a hot Key &quot;/shout Who's yer Daddy, Spiroc Lord?&quot;<br>
Spiroc Lord says &quot;REDORIOUS!&quot;    <br>
hehe :&gt;<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;&gt;Isles 1-3&lt;&lt;&lt;<br>
Faerie, (Dojorn), Azarak, Gorgalosk<br>
<br>
These are pretty standard. Faerie Isle is starting isle, note that using any spell that harms another player, AOE debuff etc will aggro the test givers below and you will get whacked out. <br>
  You dont have to do Dojorn isle its for monk epic, though Dojorn drops some nice items. He has a very bad magic based AOE and is nukeable, but Gwan the monk epic mob is only hit by lures (so mages dont bother) Prepare for several wipeouts to get Dojorn and the blasdestroms who assist him, DS rock.<br>
  Azarak isle has tons of mobs, flying critters will show you the first problems with pets getting stuck to high and stopping melee engaging. Azarack isle is aggro, go up with invis and see invis.<br>
 Gorgalosk the eyes have horrible magic resistance, use fire, they really need Mala/Malo/Tash<br>
<br>
Isle 4 Spiroc<br>
Personally I wouldn't advise using pets here unless youre very careful, the birds AOE and can thus aggro pets. Pulls generally result in around 6-8 mobs at a time, a nightmare for enchanters. So be careful.<br>
 Spiroc Lord is only hit by lures, and he Death Touches.<br>
 Island is aggro, go up with inis see invis.<br>
<br>
Isle 5 pegasus<br>
Paladins pull this, mobs are high lvl and tough, after debuffs spells will land but get in meleer ange. They split into multiples so beware. Long tough fights.<br>
<br>
Isle 6 bee Isle.<br>
Ah this is fun!! 3 bees, one splits into more..kinda like a hydra effect. All mobs only hit by lures. Very long nasty fight, DS tanks, use pet wisely (get it on rear of mobs if can they will enrage) careful it doesnt stick on flying mob up high,and drop mod rods for healers. Safe spot is back of the giant cog, isle is aggro so need invis see invis.<br>
<br>
Isle 7 Drake Isle<br>
No pets!! The warping will aggro like hell if you do.<br>
As a lvl 60 mage, after debuffs, the black drakes (heartstealer) take 1/2 damage roughly, green drakes (fatesealer)resist everything!!!!, blue drakes (windrider) fire hits well. Undine sprirts are cake easy to kill. The sister I cannot say what hits her I ate the DT :&gt;<br>
 Rememebr and Kill EVERYTHING to get your crowns. 24 hour spawn here may need to camp clear again next day.<br>
 Isle is not aggro but the sister is.<br>
<br>
Isle 7  Butterfly Isle<br>
Pretty Butterly! Again I took the DT so cant say what lands but I know that pets can stick it up high out of melee range if not careful<br>
